<% provide(:title, 'Divide Goods') %>
<% provide(:description, "Spliddit's goods calculator fairly divides jewelry, artworks, electronics, toys, furniture, financial assets, or even an entire estate between two or more people.") %>

<%= render 'banner' %>

<div class="page-content">
    <div class="wrap">
        <h1>Three or More People</h1>
        <p>Spliddit's goods calculator fairly divides jewelry, artworks, electronics, toys, furniture, financial assets, or even an entire estate between three or more people. You begin by providing a list of items that you wish to divide and a list of recipients. We then send the recipients links where they specify how much they believe each item is worth. Our algorithm uses these evaluations to propose a fair division of the items among the recipients.</p>

        <div class="start-bar">
            <p style="text-align:center">
                <a class="btn" href="<%= root_url + 'apps/goods/demo?people=3' %>" style="display:inline;margin:.5em">Live Demo</a>
                <a class="btn" href="<%= new_dividing_goods_instance_path(people: 3) %>" style="display:inline;margin:.5em">Start <span>&raquo;</span></a>
            </p>
        </div><!--.start-bar-->  
    
        <h1>Fairness Properties</h1>
                
        <div class="content-block" id="max-share">

            <div class="align-right">

                <h2 class="mobile">Maximin share</h2>

                <div class="cake-circle">
                    <%= image_tag "cake/ppl-plate.png", width: 245, height: 244, class: "ppl-plate" %>
                    <%= image_tag "cake/cake.png", width: 112, height: 62, class: "cake-full" %>
                    <%= image_tag "cake/knife-slice.png", width: 135, height: 109, class: "knife-slice" %>
                    <%= image_tag "cake/yaaaycake1.png", width: 73, height: 58, class: "yaaaycake1" %>
                    <%= image_tag "cake/yaaaycake2.png", width: 98, height: 71, class: "yaaaycake2" %>
                </div><!--.circle-->
                <p class="refresh cake"><a href="#" title="Replay">refresh</a></p>
            
            </div><!--.align-right-->

            <div class="property-info left">

                <h2 class="desktop">Maximin share</h2>
                <p>A participant's maximin share is the amount of value she could guarantee if she were to divide the goods into bundles herself, and then other participants were allowed to choose their bundle before her.</p>
                <p>We guarantee each participant at least two thirds of her maximin share. In practice, it is extremely likely that each participant will receive at least her full maximin share.</p>
            
            </div>

        </div><!--.content-block-->

        <div class="content-block last" id="envy-free">
        
            <div class="align-left">

                <h2 class="mobile">Envy-freeness</h2>
                
                <div class="family-circle run-animation" id="test">
                    <div class="family">
                        <%= image_tag "itemshift/family.png", width: 241, height: 253, class: "bodies" %>
                        <%= image_tag "itemshift/smiles.png", width: 181, height: 155, class: "smiles" %>
                        <%= image_tag "itemshift/frowns.png", width: 181, height: 149, class: "frowns" %>
                        <%= image_tag "itemshift/football.png", width: 67, height: 36, class: "football" %>
                        <%= image_tag "itemshift/bottle.png", width: 31, height: 57, class: "bottle" %>
                        <%= image_tag "itemshift/purse.png", width: 59, height: 59, class: "purse" %>
                    </div><!--.family-->
                </div><!--.circle-->
                <p class="refresh items"><a href="#" title="Replay">refresh</a></p>
            
            </div><!--.align-left-->

            <div class="property-info right">

                <h2 class="desktop">Envy-freeness</h2>

                <p>A division of goods is envy-free if each participant believes that her bundle of goods is at least as valuable as every other participant's bundle. In other words, no participant would want to swap places with another participant.</p>
                <p>We compute an envy-free allocation if possible, but this property cannot be guaranteed.</p>
                
            </div>

        </div><!--.content-block-->

        <div class="start-bar">
            <p style="text-align:center">
                <a class="btn" href="<%= root_url + 'apps/goods/demo?people=3' %>" style="display:inline;margin:.5em">Live Demo</a>
                <a class="btn" href="<%= new_dividing_goods_instance_path(people: 3) %>" style="display:inline;margin:.5em">Start <span>&raquo;</span></a>
            </p>
        </div><!--.start-bar-->  


        <h1>Algorithm Overview</h1>
        <p>Our algorithm considers several levels of fairness, including <a href="#max-share">maximin share</a>, proportionality, and <a href="#envy-free">envy-freeness</a>, and finds the highest feasible level of fairness. The lowest level of fairness, approximate maximin share, can always be guaranteed. Subject to this fairness constraint, the algorithm maximizes social welfare â€” the sum of points the participants assign to their allocated bundles of goods. The optimization problem is formulated as an <a target="_blank" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integer_linear_program">integer linear program</a> and solved via <a target="_blank" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CPLEX">CPLEX</a>.</p>
        <p><strong>Reference:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~arielpro/papers/mms.pdf">"Fair Enough: Guaranteeing Approximate Maximin Shares"</a>, by Ariel D. Procaccia and Junxing Wang.</p>

        <div class="start-bar">
            <p style="text-align:center">
                <a class="btn" href="<%= root_url + 'apps/goods/demo?people=3' %>" style="display:inline;margin:.5em">Live Demo</a>
                <a class="btn" href="<%= new_dividing_goods_instance_path(people: 3) %>" style="display:inline;margin:.5em">Start <span>&raquo;</span></a>
            </p>
        </div><!--.start-bar-->  

    </div><!--.wrap-->
</div><!--.page-content-->